{"word":"ἑκούσιος","slug":"ἑκούσιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἑκούσιος</b></el> <el>(ἑκούσιος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἑκών'><el>ἑκών</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>of actions, <i>voluntary</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>τὰ ἑκούσια</el> <i>voluntary acts</i>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>τὰ ἀκούσια</el>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>rarely, like <el>ἑκών</el>, of persons, <i>willing, acting of free will</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-ίως</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; so, <el>ἐξ ἑκουσίας</el> (<a href='S:scilicet'>sc.</a> <el>γνώμης</el>) <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>καθ' ἑκουσίαν</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}